    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-25T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="571"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d571">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (<persName corresp="#p_I2"
                        >Italy</persName>)/6–2345: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 571<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in <persName corresp="#p_Y1">Yugoslavia</persName>
                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SH2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-25T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 25, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>158. <persName corresp="#p_TMJB1">Tito</persName>’s statement that <gloss
                        target="#t_VG1">VG</gloss> civil govt problem is still pending (your 197,
                    June 23<note n="1" xml:id="d571fn1">
                        <ref target="#d568">Document No, 568</ref>.</note>) is incomprehensible in
                    view of clear stipulations Art. 3 of Belgrade agreement, (Sent Belgrade as 158,
                        <gloss target="#t_rptd1">rptd</gloss>. Caserta as 617.) In your discussions
                    with Yugo officials you should present this view (see <gloss target="#t_para1"
                        >para</gloss> 2 our 151, June 23 [<hi rend="italic">22</hi>]; 607 to
                        Caserta<note n="2" xml:id="d571fn2">
                        <ref target="#d565">Document No. 565</ref>.</note>). Keep before Yugo govt
                    the thought that sympathy in this country for just Yugo claims will largely
                    depend on strict fulfillment of signed commitments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">W[illiam] P[hillips]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
